Chicken, Spinach and Sweet Potato Soup

2 32oz chicken stock containers
1 medium sweet potato peeled and cubed
1 large russet potato  peeled and cubed
3 cups fresh baby spinach leaves 
2 cups cooked roast chicken meat 
2 clove garlic, minced 
3 celery stalks cubed
1/2 large onion diced
salt and ground black pepper to taste
1 teaspoon dried thyme
1 tablespoon butter


1. Saute onion and garlic in butter until slightly brown over medium-high heat
2. Add chicken stock, thyme and potatoes. Cook until potato is soft enough to pierce with a fork, about 10 minutes. 
3. Stir in spinach, chicken, and celery; simmer until spinach is wilted and broth is reduced slightly, 10 to 15 minutes more. 
4. Season with salt and pepper.

Original source: http://allrecipes.com/recipe/246224/chicken-sweet-potato-and-spinach-soup/
